stylometry: Optimization is when you want to find the minimal costs or maximum profits possible of a given situation/problem. An example would be if you are selling tables and chairs and it costs X amount to produce one and Y amount to produce the other and then you can sell each one different amounts but you have limits on materials and time for each one; how many of each one would you sell to maximize profits. The components of linear programming are; decision variables which are also known as changing cells, objective functions which are also known as target cells, and constraints which are the limits assigned to the problem.
